UPDATE: AMES has cancelled school today. Disregard the late start schedule.

AMES will be on a 2-hr delay this morning. Staff will be there at 10:30, and classes will begin at 11:00am. Buses will pick-up students 2hrs later than their usual time.

As before, if you do not feel it is safe to send or transport your students to school, please keep them home. The safety of our students is our priority. AMES administration and faculty will work with students impacted by this situation.

Murray Journal
January 28 at 3:29 PM ¬∑

The Academy for Math, Engineering & Science recently hosted 22 robots in a friendly preseason game of ‚Äúroboblasters,‚Äù which was designed around improving skills for the 13 participating schools‚Äô robotic students. At the challenge, Cottonwood High won, with Jordan High coming in second and AMES, third. In the business plan portion, Judge Memorial won, with AMES, Hillcrest, West High and Cottonwood placing second to fifth, respectively. The AMES challenge is the 5th annual December competition preparing students for the FIRST robotics challenge.

A student photo of students photographing. Today, the Photography students were shooting a Graphlex Speed Graphic Pacemaker camera that's nearly 70 years old. Learn by doing!
